[{"short_id":"0zha79","created_at":"2026-07-04T07:35:37.000-05:00","title":"Who's Hiring? - Support Edition - Q3 2026","url":"","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWelcome to the trial post of a \"Who's Hiring?\" call for non-software engineer positions!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs we try to kick this off, I would love community input on things like;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhat other details would you like employers to provide in their initial reply?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWhat frequency do we want? Quarterly? Monthly? Every other week?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAre there any other roles that should be considered for these posts?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny job postings should be geared towards needed company roles other than Software Engineer, such as customer support, data entry, field technician, marketing, purchasers, etc...that list can get quite long, depending on the size of the company and type of business.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe'll keep this initial post conversational for the sake of getting community input about what we want to see and refining the template. Should this garner enough interest and stick, future posts should result in only/mostly job postings in the comments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePost Template\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCompany Website:\u003c/strong\u003e [ url ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCulture:\u003c/strong\u003e [ brief description of company mission and culture ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAvailable Position(s):\u003c/strong\u003e [ e.g customer support, technical writer, social media manager, service technician, etc. ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJob Type:\u003c/strong\u003e [ onsite | remote | hybrid ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eJob Level:\u003c/strong\u003e [ entry | junior | senior | etc ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDescription:\u003c/strong\u003e [ brief description of the role and responsibilities ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExperience:\u003c/strong\u003e [ necessary skills or experience to perform the job ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCompensation:\u003c/strong\u003e [ salary \u0026amp; benefits ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAdditional Notes:\u003c/strong\u003e [ any info specific to the role that doesn't fit in the above categories ]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eContact:\u003c/strong\u003e [ email ]\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Welcome to the trial post of a \"Who's Hiring?\" call for non-software engineer positions! \r\n\r\nAs we try to kick this off, I would love community input on things like; \r\n\r\n1. What other details would you like employers to provide in their initial reply? \r\n2. What frequency do we want? Quarterly? Monthly? Every other week? \r\n3. Are there any other roles that should be considered for these posts? \r\n\r\nAny job postings should be geared towards needed company roles other than Software Engineer, such as customer support, data entry, field technician, marketing, purchasers, etc...that list can get quite long, depending on the size of the company and type of business. \r\n\r\nWe'll keep this initial post conversational for the sake of getting community input about what we want to see and refining the template. Should this garner enough interest and stick, future posts should result in only/mostly job postings in the comments. \r\n\r\n## Post Template\r\n\r\n**Company Website:** [ url ]\r\n\r\n**Culture:** [ brief description of company mission and culture ]\r\n\r\n**Available Position(s):** [ e.g customer support, technical writer, social media manager, service technician, etc. ]\r\n\r\n**Job Type:** [ onsite | remote | hybrid ]\r\n\r\n**Job Level:** [ entry | junior | senior | etc ]\r\n\r\n**Description:** [ brief description of the role and responsibilities ]\r\n\r\n**Experience:** [ necessary skills or experience to perform the job ]\r\n\r\n**Compensation:** [ salary \u0026 benefits ]\r\n\r\n**Additional Notes:** [ any info specific to the role that doesn't fit in the above categories ]\r\n\r\n**Contact:** [ email ]","submitter_user":"tinsmith","user_is_author":true,"tags":["job"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0zha79","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/0zha79/who_s_hiring_support_edition_q3_2026"},{"short_id":"qmnpkm","created_at":"2026-07-04T07:28:37.000-05:00","title":"FreeBSD ate my ram","url":"https://crocidb.com/post/freebsd-ate-my-ram/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"orib","user_is_author":false,"tags":["freebsd","osdev"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qmnpkm","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qmnpkm/freebsd_ate_my_ram"},{"short_id":"be22hc","created_at":"2026-07-04T06:57:02.000-05:00","title":"Reducing Assumptions, Exploding Your Code","url":"https://ryelang.org/blog/posts/reducing_assumptions_but_exploding/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"refaktor","user_is_author":true,"tags":["plt"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/be22hc","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/be22hc/reducing_assumptions_exploding_your"},{"short_id":"ekxkqq","created_at":"2026-07-04T06:53:48.000-05:00","title":"Dunya Kirkali - Your organization as a Graph","url":"https://www.wearedevelopers.com/en/videos/2051/your-organization-as-a-graph","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"dunyakirkali","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ekxkqq","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ekxkqq/dunya_kirkali_your_organization_as_graph"},{"short_id":"avqu6k","created_at":"2026-07-04T06:30:50.000-05:00","title":"Developer Verification – LineageOS","url":"https://lineageos.org/Developer-Verification/","score